text: Tes Schouten (born 31 December 2000) is a Dutch swimmer. She competed in the women's 100 metre breaststroke at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships. In 2017, she won the silver medal in the girls' 100 metre breaststroke at the 2017 European Junior Swimming Championships held in Netanya, Israel. ==References== Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:Dutch female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:European Games competitors for the Netherlands Category:Swimmers at the 2015 European Games Category:European Games medalists in swimming Category:European Games silver medalists for the Netherlands Category:Dutch female breaststroke swimmers
